 &lt;p&gt;⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-highest-altitude/&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a biker going on a road trip. The road trip &lt;span class=&#34;orange&#34;&gt;consists of&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;code&gt;n + 1&lt;/code&gt;  points at different &lt;span class=&#34;orange&#34;&gt;altitudes&lt;/span&gt;. The biker starts his trip on point  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;  with altitude equal  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are given an integer array  &lt;code&gt;gain&lt;/code&gt;  of length  &lt;code&gt;n&lt;/code&gt;  where  &lt;code&gt;gain[i]&lt;/code&gt;  is the &lt;strong&gt;net gain in altitude&lt;/strong&gt; between points  &lt;code&gt;i&lt;/code&gt; ​​​​​​ and  &lt;code&gt;i + 1&lt;/code&gt;  for all  &lt;code&gt;(0 &amp;lt;= i &amp;lt; n)&lt;/code&gt; . Return &lt;em&gt;the &lt;strong&gt;highest altitude&lt;/strong&gt; of a point&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: gain = [-5,1,5,0,-7]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: 1&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: The altitudes are [0,-5,-4,1,1,-6]. The highest is 1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input&lt;/strong&gt;: gain = [-4,-3,-2,-1,4,3,2]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output&lt;/strong&gt;: 0&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation&lt;/strong&gt;: The altitudes are [0,-4,-7,-9,-10,-6,-3,-1]. The highest is 0.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
